There are .gitignore templates&gt; suited for pretty much any project. I&rsquo;m going to share the .gitignore that I recently been using for my web projects. It&rsquo;s and extended verison of github&rsquo;s global .gitignore&gt;.
Here is the gist&gt;:
//this will affect all the git repos git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore //update files since .ignore won't if already tracked git rm --cached &lt;file&gt; # Compiled source # ################### *.com *.class *.dll *.exe *.
